```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 13, 5, 19, 8, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'personalizedrefrigerator', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 919659760, 'comment_body': "```suggestion
	/** Value to use on small-width displays */    
	sm?: number;
	/** Value to use on medium-width displays */
	md?: number;
	/** Value to use on large-width displays */
	lg?: number;
	/** Value to use on extra-large displays */
	xl?: number;
	/** Value to use on extra-extra-large displays */
	xxl?: number;
```

I think that documentation comments could be helpful here (I'm suggesting documentation comments because they have good support in `vscode`)!

Additionally, be sure not to mix tabs and spaces!", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 13, 5, 24, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'personalizedrefrigerator', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 919660757, 'comment_body': '```suggestion
	if (width >= 481 && md != null) {
```

If I run this:
```
$ node
Welcome to Node.js v16.16.0.
Type ".help" for more information.
> !!0
false
> !!1
true
```
As such, if someone sets `md` (or `lg`, `xl`, or `xxl`) to `0`, this conditional won't trigger.

(I'm suggesting `!=` and not `!==` because `md != null` returns `false` if `md` is `undefined`, but `md !== null` returns `true` if `md` is `undefined`).', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 13, 5, 26, 12, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'personalizedrefrigerator', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 919661982, 'comment_body': 'It might make sense to make this a `private` method.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 13, 5, 28, 48, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'personalizedrefrigerator', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 919885878, 'comment_body': "Thanks for this. I'll look through it.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 13, 9, 57, 37, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Tolu-Mals', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 919886243, 'comment_body': 'Noted, thanks', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 13, 9, 57, 58, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Tolu-Mals', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 919962878, 'comment_body': 'Thanks for this.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 13, 11, 23, 8, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Tolu-Mals', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 919965286, 'comment_body': "Wasn't sure initially if getResponsiveValue should accept a value of zero, but I think it makes sense that it does. Thank you.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 13, 11, 26, 11, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Tolu-Mals', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 920006873, 'comment_body': '@laurent22 Is it okay to use Typescript directly for testing?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 13, 12, 16, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Tolu-Mals', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 927485530, 'comment_body': "Eventually we might do that, but for now let's keep using the compiled .js files for testing.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 22, 9, 45, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'laurent22', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 927487566, 'comment_body': 'Good point about the comments but should be single lines one `//`. Please only use that type of comments', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 22, 9, 48, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'laurent22', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 927488591, 'comment_body': "You're mixing tabs and spaces here. Please make sure you run `yarn run linter ./` from the root of the repository before committing.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 22, 9, 49, 16, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'laurent22', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 927574541, 'comment_body': 'Alright, noted.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 22, 11, 48, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Tolu-Mals', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 927574742, 'comment_body': "Noted, I'll fix that.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 22, 11, 49, 18, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Tolu-Mals', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928124271, 'comment_body': 'Wait, actually @personalizedrefrigerator set it up with ts-jest, is that right? In that case, yes please use this for this particular package.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 23, 13, 33, 12, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'laurent22', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928663399, 'comment_body': 'This can be simplified using the [`??` operator](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Nullish_coalescing_operator):
